Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.43,0:05:47.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&H42B4F8&}布莱恩·德·帕尔马电影
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.83,0:05:51.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&H42B4F8&}约翰·特拉沃尔塔
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.33,0:06:01.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs24\fsp2}爆胎
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.45,0:01:11.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,里面的，你们停下好吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, will you guys shut up in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.87,0:01:14.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,芭芭拉\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Barbara.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.90,0:01:16.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦，糟糕\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.40,0:01:29.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是在干什么？我正在努力复习期末考\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What the hell is going on in here? I am trying to study for a final.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.76,0:01:32.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对，我们也有期末考 你听过现代舞吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, we have finals too. Ever hear of modern dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.76,0:01:36.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你不能边听音乐边学习吗？  - 不，我不能边听音乐边学习\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Can't you study to music?- No, I can't study to music.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.55,0:01:38.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,调低音量，否则我就去找苏了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Turn it down or do I have to go to Sue?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.51,0:01:40.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 那就去找苏吧  - 滚开\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}-Go to Sue, then.  - Fuck off.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.27,0:01:44.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我要去苏那儿  - 我要去苏那儿\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I'm going to Sue.  - I'm going to Sue.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.62,0:02:01.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 离开我  - 怎么了？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Get off of me. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.92,0:02:09.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,外面有人，快，外面有人\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, there's somebody out there. Come on. There's somebody out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.00,0:02:12.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 得了，外面没有人  - 真有\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- There's nobody out there. - There is.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.02,0:02:18.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 冷静  - 我没法冷静\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Calm down. - I can't calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.14,0:02:24.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你最好想想办法，因为有这些迪斯科音乐我没法学习\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You better take care of it, cos I can't study with this disco music.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.98,0:02:29.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧，来\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}All right, move. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.11,0:02:32.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,瞧，小告密者带回大告密者\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, look. The little fink brought back the master fink.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.81,0:02:35.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,（浴室）
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.30,0:02:42.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 音乐并不吵  - 不，很吵\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- The music's not loud. - Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.88,0:03:28.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天，那个尖叫声真烂\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}God, that scream is terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.25,0:03:33.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你勒死猫了吗，弄出这声音？  - 就是你听见的那只，是她的声音\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- What cat did you strangle to get that?  - The cat that you heard. That's her voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.10,0:03:35.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你没有配音？  - 没有\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You didn't dub that? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.62,0:03:37.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 那是她的声音？  - 对\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- That's hers? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.31,0:03:39.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 真的吗？  - 对\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Oh, really? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.98,0:03:42.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再放一遍，我想听听那个尖叫声\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Run it again. I wanna hear the scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.24,0:03:54.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 重放？  - 对\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- ...Run it? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.00,0:04:03.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,去掉所有声效，只留尖叫声\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}And kill all the effects except for the scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.04,0:04:15.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,去掉\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Kill it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.76,0:04:19.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你说对了，是她，真烂\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're right. It's hers. And it's shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.62,0:04:23.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,杰克，我雇那女孩不是为了她的叫声，我是为了她的乳头雇的那女孩儿\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Look, Jack, I didn't hire that girl for her scream. I hired that girl for her tits.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.75,0:04:26.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那你担心什么？谁会看她尖叫呢？咱们继续吧\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Then what do you worry about? Who's gonna be watching her scream? Let's move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.08,0:04:29.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等等，好了，杰克\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Wait a minute. Come on, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.54,0:04:33.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你看，咱俩合作多少年了？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Look, how many years have we worked together?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.43,0:04:39.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我算算，我是在《血浴》遇见的你，对吧？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Let's see. I met you on Blood Bath, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.22,0:04:41.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后咱们做了《血浴2》\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}And then we did Blood Bath II.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.85,0:04:45.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们做了《血滩一日》\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}And then we did Bad Day at Blood Beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.98,0:04:48.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们做了《血妓院》\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}And then we did Bordello of Blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.15,0:04:52.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦，然后就是今天了，《合校狂暴》\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, that brings us up today. Co-ed Frenzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.94,0:04:55.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对了，我没跟你说过，不过…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}By the way, I didn't tell you this but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.28,0:04:59.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我把它看作是咱们最好的电影\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'd like to think this is our finest film.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.28,0:05:03.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 将近两年  - 哦，天，两年五部电影\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Almost two years. - Oh, God. Five films in two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.66,0:05:05.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你知道我有什么想不通吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know what I can't figure out?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.47,0:05:09.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想不通你这么聪明的人怎么还在做这种烂黄片？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I can't figure out what a smart guy like you is still doing that shit porn.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.46,0:05:11.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,得了，是你做烂黄片，我做音效\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Come on. You do the shit. I do the sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.79,0:05:16.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不，你做的太烂，那风声听起来像在厕所吹口哨\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}No, you do the shit. That wind sounds like you're whistling in the crapper.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.02,0:05:18.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是图书馆的东西，我们用过无数次了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's library stuff we used a million times.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.26,0:05:21.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,问题就在这里，我听过无数次了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}That is the trouble. I have heard it a million times.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.01,0:05:25.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 弄点新的来  - 新的风声，明白\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Get something new. - New wind. Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.31,0:05:30.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 还有那尖叫，我们必须配音  - 好吧，认识尖叫声好的人吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- And what that scream. We gotta dub that. - All right. Know any good screamers?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.02,0:05:34.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我有几个  - 你肯定有\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I got a few ideas. - I bet you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.03,0:05:36.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你操心好尖叫声，好吗\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Just worry about the scream, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.45,0:06:27.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对白宫政策铺天盖地的谴责\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}...a sweeping condemnation of White House policies.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.83,0:06:31.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同一个民调显示，迅速高涨的支持…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}The same poll gave evidence of a ground swell of support...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.42,0:06:34.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对乔治·麦克雷州长的党内提名\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}...for Governor George McRyan in his bid for the party's nomination.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.71,0:06:39.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果今天进行选举，麦克雷州长取胜易如反掌\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}If an election were held today, Governor McRyan would win hands down,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.09,0:06:44.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,票数差距显著，62%对总统的23%\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}drawing a remarkable 62 per cent of the vote to the president's 23.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.76,0:06:48.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,总统的竞选经理杰克·曼纳斯，今天早些时候告诉记者\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}The president's campaign manager, Jack Manners, told reporters earlyer today:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.73,0:06:51.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,总统必须做出一些艰难的决定\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}The president's had to make some tough decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.48,0:06:55.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过等这些政策实施后\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}But when these policies are carried out...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.52,0:07:00.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经济状况提高后—对此我们深信不疑\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and the economic climate improves, as we confidently expect it will,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.95,0:07:05.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人民会团结起来，在即将到来的初选中支持总统\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}the people will rally to support the president in the upcoming primaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.12,0:07:09.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从现在到那时会发生很多事\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}A lot can happen between now and then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.87,0:07:14.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时，国会领袖们焦虑等待麦克雷州长宣布参选\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Meanwhile leaders in congress waits anxiously for Governor McRyan to declare his candidacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.08,0:07:19.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们也许不用等太久了，州长正在贝维斯特福酒店的宴会厅\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}They may not have much longer to wait. The governor is now at the ballroom of Bellevue Stratford...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.56,0:07:24.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几分钟后，他将为自由日庆典的开幕晚餐致辞演讲\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}...where in just a few minute he is expected to address the kickoff dinner of the Liberty Day celebration.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.72,0:07:28.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有些人猜测他将利用此时机宣布参选\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Some people are guessing that he will use the occasion to throw his hat into the ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.64,0:07:31.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,情况如何，琼？贝维斯特福那边有消息吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What about it, Joan? Any word from the Bellevue Stratford yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.64,0:07:35.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还没有，比尔，不过一旦有消息我们将直播\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Not yet, Bill, but as soon as there is, we will be going there live.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.40,0:07:40.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们都知道，自由日是费城庆典中最受热烈期待之一\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}As we all know, Liberty Day is one of the most eagerly awaited of all Philadelphia celebrations.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.86,0:07:43.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过今年将格外特别\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}But this year it's going to be extra special.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.91,0:07:49.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自由钟上次敲响已过整整百年，为此百年纪念增光…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It is exactly 100 years since the Liberty Bell was last rung. To honour this centennial,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.29,0:07:52.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,周六将有一次游行，沿沃克街而行…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}there will be a parade on Saturday down Walk street...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.37,0:07:57.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,游行终点是佩恩登陆地，那里将有盛大烟火表演\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}...will end up at Penn's Landing with a spectacular display of fireworks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.88,0:08:01.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此外，一座自由钟全尺寸复制品已经制成\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}In addition, a full-size replica of the Liberty Bell has been made...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.55,0:08:05.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它由全美各州小学生们捐出的硬币制作\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}...from pennies donated by schoolchildren from every state in the Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.01,0:08:09.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,琼，我了解到，他们将在佩恩登陆地烟火结束后敲响它\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Joan, I understand that they'll be ringing it after the fireworks at Penn's Landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.64,0:08:11.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没错\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.64,0:08:14.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等等，我们得到此刻贝维斯特福的消息\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hold it. I think we're getting something from the Bellevue Stratford right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.02,0:08:18.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让我们转向我们“城市之眼”的政治通讯记者，弗兰克·唐纳休\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Let's go live to our 'Eye on the City'  political correspondent, Frank Donahue,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.86,0:08:21.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他正在贝维斯特福酒店的自由钟前\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}at the Liberty Ball at the Bellevue Stratford Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.07,0:08:26.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,弗兰克，你看起来精神很好，你跟州长谈过了吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Frank, you look fabulous. Have you spoken with the governor yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.11,0:08:29.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对，琼，但只是简短交谈，他刚到达\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yes, Joan, but only briefly. He arrived only moments ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.41,0:08:34.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我的确问过州长，到目前为止他对今年自由日庆典有何看法\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I did ask the governor regarding his impression so far of this year's Liberty Day Jubilee.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.62,0:08:36.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,州长说，他来到此地倍感荣幸\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}The governor said he was honoured to be here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.79,0:08:41.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他计划出席游行，当然还有周六晚上敲响新钟的活动\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and he plans to attend the parade and of cource the ringing of the new bell on Saturday night.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.01,0:08:45.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,州长继续说，他感觉自由钟沉默如此长的时间是一种羞耻\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}The governor went on to say, Joan, he felt it a shame the Liberty Bell had been silenced for so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.85,0:08:49.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他正期待一个新的自由之声响彻这片大陆\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}He looked forward to a new voice of liberty throughout the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.64,0:08:55.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,州长此刻正在问候几位老朋友，我们了解到他还将加入宴会厅的晚宴\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}The governor is now greeting some old friends and we understand that he will be enjoying a meal in the ballroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.73,0:09:00.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过他的人告诉我们，餐后他将立刻对我们讲话\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}But his people have told us that he will speak to us when he finishes that meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.61,0:09:05.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里是弗兰克·唐纳休，“城市之眼”新闻，贝维斯特福报导\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm Frank Donahue. 'Eye on the City' News, Bellevue Stratford.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.86,0:09:09.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢，弗兰克，我们待会儿国际新闻再转到你那边\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Thank you, Frank. We'll be getting back to you later on the abroad cast.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.41,0:09:13.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与此同时，今晚其它新闻，一场教师罢工…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Meanwhile, in other news this evening, there was a teacher's strike...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.76,0:09:55.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,咱们沿着河边散会儿步吧\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}...Let's take a walk along the river here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.08,0:10:01.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗯，好\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mm. Nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.50,0:10:06.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 戴维，看，有人在桥上  - 咱们别操这份心了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- David, look. Someone's on the bridge. - Let's not worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.51,0:10:08.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他正盯着我们  - 谁管呢？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- He's staring right at us. - Who cares?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.80,0:10:10.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我管  - 贝琪\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I care. - Betsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.55,0:10:13.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我不想再待在这里，走吧  - 那好\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I don't wanna stay here anymore. Let's go. - Yeah, OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.68,0:10:15.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他在干什么  - 我不知道\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- What is he doing? - I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.97,0:10:21.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他是什么人，偷窥者什么的？  - 哦，谁管呢？咱们从这边下去吧\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- What is he, a Peeping Tom or something? - Oh, who cares? Let's walk down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.72,0:10:57.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,（维萨黑肯沃克）
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.82,0:11:56.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,老天爷\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.61,0:12:35.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,老天，请救救我\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, God. Please help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.33,0:12:43.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,带我离开这里，求你\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Get me out of here, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.59,0:12:53.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦，老天\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh. Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.28,0:14:00.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,（限急诊出入）
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.99,0:14:10.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,（保安 警察 付费电话）
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.25,0:14:13.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 砰的一声？  - 对，大概是砰的一声\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- A bang? - Yeah, some sort of a bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.80,0:14:14.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哪里传来的？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.20,0:14:16.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不确定是哪里\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm not sure where.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.05,0:14:17.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你正面对汽车？  - 对\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You were facing the car? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.92,0:14:19.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦，你听见的是爆胎声\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, you heard the blowout.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.55,0:14:22.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对，我听见爆胎声了，但第一声我听到的是砰\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yes sir, I  heard the blowout, but the first sound I heard was a bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.05,0:14:24.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 是某种回声吧  - 不是\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Some kind of an echo. - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.22,0:14:27.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,听着，我知道回声什么样，我是做声音的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Look, I know what an echo sounds like. I'm a sound man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.60,0:14:30.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且砰声是在爆胎之前\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}And the bang was before the blowout.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.52,0:14:34.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你当时在那边做什么？  - 我在为一部电影录声音\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- What were you doin' up there? - I was recording sounds for a movie I work in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.52,0:14:37.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你录下了这次事故的声音？  - 对\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You recorded the accident? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.15,0:14:40.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那之后发生了什么\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What happened after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.10,0:14:43.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接着那辆车冲出道路进了小河里，我…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well then the car went off the road into the creek and I...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.87,0:14:46.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 后来你做了什么？  - 我正要告诉你我做了什么\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- What did you do then? - I'm tryin' to tell you what I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.45,0:14:50.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我跑下去，跳进河里，拉出那女孩\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I ran down, jumped in the creek and pulled out the girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.71,0:14:53.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 有一个女孩儿？  - 对，有个女孩儿\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- There was a girl?  - Yes, there was a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.50,0:14:57.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 什么样的女孩？  - 我带来的那女孩，房间里那女孩\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- What girl? - The girl I brought here. The girl in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.30,0:14:59.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她当时在车里？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}She was inside the car?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.01,0:15:02.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 对  - 你确定？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Yes. - Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.26,0:15:05.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我又没开玩笑，我当然确定了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I wasn't bobbing for apples. Of course I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.89,0:15:08.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水下八英尺可是相当黑暗的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, look, it can get pretty dark under eight feet of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.47,0:15:09.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你这是在干嘛？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What're you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.57,0:15:14.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这算不算是获取客观目击者的证词？如果是的话就算了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Is this known as obtaining objective eyewitness testimony? If it is, forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.86,0:15:17.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们得让担架通过，大家退后\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}We gotta get the stretcher through. Come on peaple, step back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.29,0:15:34.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,医生，她怎么样？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Doctor. How is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.38,0:15:35.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很幸运\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Very lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.80,0:15:39.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,轻微休克，有些割伤和瘀伤，没有大伤\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mild shock, some cuts and bruises. No major injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.76,0:15:41.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我能看看她吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Can I see her?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.11,0:15:43.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她也许在睡觉，她服了镇定剂\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}She might be asleep. She's sedated.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.34,0:15:46.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我就去说声再见  - 别待太久\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I'll just say goodbye. - Don't stay too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.31,0:15:50.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么样？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}How you doin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.44,0:15:56.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我的包在你那儿吗？  - 不在\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Do you have my purse? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.86,0:16:00.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我肯定警察会找到的，是我就不担心\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm sure the police'll find it. I wouldn't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.36,0:16:01.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我知道\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.15,0:16:04.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你要去哪儿？  - 我得走了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Where are you going? - I have to leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.24,0:16:07.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,什么？等一下，我觉得你应该回到床上去\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What? Wait a minute. I think you'd better get back to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.87,0:16:09.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得他们还没治疗完呢\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I don't think they're finished with you yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.90,0:16:11.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来吧，上去\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Come on, up. Up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.16,0:16:14.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 就一会儿  - 好吧\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Just for a minute. - All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.04,0:16:16.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你感觉怎么样？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}So how do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.25,0:16:21.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他说我很幸运——那个医生\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}He said I was lucky-- the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.13,0:16:23.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对，他应该在场，对吧\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah. He should've been there, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.89,0:16:29.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 谢谢你救我出来  - 没事\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Thanks for getting me out. - No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.97,0:16:33.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我那时没注意到你这么漂亮，身上好多泥，脸…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I didn't realise you were this pretty, with all that mud all over you. Face...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.06,0:16:36.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我都没化妆呢\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I don't have any make-up on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.27,0:16:40.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦，别担心，没事，这里是医院\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, don't worry about it. It's fine. It's a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.87,0:16:44.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你是谁？  - 我叫杰克·泰瑞，你呢？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Who are you? - I'm Jack Terry. Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.16,0:16:49.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 莎莉  - 莎莉？幸会，莎莉\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Sally. - Sally? Nice to meet you, Sally.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.75,0:17:03.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你要走了吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Are you leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.42,0:17:06.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对，我得走了，不过…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, I gotta go. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.43,0:17:10.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等你出院，咱们找时间去喝一杯如何？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What'd you say, when you get outta here, we have a drink sometime?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.70,0:17:12.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用玻璃杯喝\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}In a glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.35,0:17:14.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 好啊  - 好的，你保重\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Sure. - OK. You take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.43,0:17:16.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,今晚怎么样？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}How about tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.90,0:17:18.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不，我觉得不行，莎莉，今晚不行\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}No, I don't think so, Sally. Not tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.48,0:17:21.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过我告诉你，我会问问医生你什么时候能出院\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}But I'll tell you what I'm gonna do. I'll check withthe doctor see when you get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.51,0:17:25.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他想要留我做观察  - 等等，莎莉，你真的得待在床上\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- He wants to keep me for observation. - Wait a minute, Sally, you really gotta stay in bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.57,0:17:28.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不想被观察\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I don't like to be observed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.20,0:17:31.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉，但这事我真帮不了什么\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm sorry, but there's really nothing I can do about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.20,0:17:35.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拜托，我真的不喜欢医院，我得离开这里\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Please. I really don't like hospitals. I've got to get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.46,0:17:37.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧，我跟你约定\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}All right. I'll make you a deal, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.39,0:17:39.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样子，你留在这里，我去拿你的衣服\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}This's the deal. You stay here, I'll get your clothes,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.08,0:17:44.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等我回来，我们就出去喝一杯，好吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}and when I come back, we'll go out and have a drink, OK? All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.09,0:17:47.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我需要鞋子和一件外套  - 对，我去拿\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I need shoes and a coat. - Yes. I'll get them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.93,0:17:50.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但要是你不留下，我就不回来了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}But if you don't stay, I'm not comin' back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.76,0:17:52.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 好的  - 好\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- OK. - All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.41,0:18:14.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看起来她没什么事\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It looks like she's gonna be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.79,0:18:18.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个人，杰克·泰瑞，把她救出车子的，他在那边\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}This guy, Jack Terry, that took her out of the car, he's over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.58,0:18:23.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他真是麻烦，我不知道咱们怎么能捂住这家伙的嘴\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}He's being a real horse's ass. I don't know how we're gonna keep the lid on this guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.59,0:18:27.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,找些人来，我要封锁这里，我不要这里乱哄哄的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Get some men here. I want this place sealed. I don't want this circus.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.30,0:18:31.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长官，就是这家伙，事情发生时他在场，他看到了整件事\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sir, this is the guy. He was right there when it happened. He saw the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.39,0:18:36.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他就是目击者？  - 对，他叫杰克·泰瑞，他说他把那女孩拉出车子\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- He's the one who saw it? - Yes. He's name is Jack Terry. He says he pulled the girl out of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.06,0:18:44.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我要跟你谈谈，还有那女孩儿，她在哪里？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I wanna talk to you. And to the girl too. Where is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.48,0:18:46.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 她在那里面  - 她在睡觉\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- She's in there. - She's asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.48,0:18:49.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你想跟我谈就快点，今晚我受够了，我要回家\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}And if you wanna talk to me, make it quick, couse I've had enough tonight, I wanna go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.95,0:18:53.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 有没有什么地方咱们可以私下谈的？  - 是，长官，我来找\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Is there someplace we can talk in private?  - Yes sir, I'll take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.49,0:18:57.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你能不能替我们派人保卫这房间？  - 我要这些人出去\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Would you secure that room for us? - I want these men checked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.16,0:19:01.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 警官，这里怎么了？  - 车祸，有人受害\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Officer, what's goin' on here? - Car accident. Guy got killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.33,0:19:05.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我知道，但这么大阵仗干嘛？  - 你知道那人是麦克雷吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I know, but what's the big deal? - Did you know the guy was McRyan?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.38,0:19:06.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是麦克雷州长？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's Governor McRyan?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.88,0:19:11.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,担架上的死尸曾经可能成为咱们下一任总统\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}That stiff on the stretcher was probably our next president.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.01,0:19:14.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 见鬼，我本要投他的票  - 老天爷\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Hell, he had my vote. - Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.77,0:19:19.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,咱们进里面谈\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Let's talk in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.90,0:19:33.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你把那女孩拉出车？  - 对\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You pulled the girl out of that car? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.24,0:19:36.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么，我希望你忘掉她\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, I would like for you to forget about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.93,0:19:38.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,忘记你曾经见过她\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Forget you ever saw her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.58,0:19:41.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等一下\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.54,0:19:42.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你是谁？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.24,0:19:44.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我名叫劳伦斯·亨利\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}My name is Lawrence Henry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.50,0:19:47.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我为麦克雷州长工作  - 啊\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I worked for Governor McRyan. - Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.75,0:19:49.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他也是一位朋友\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}He was also a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.25,0:19:53.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他是我的朋友\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}He was my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.80,0:19:57.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,瞧，对于州长我深感遗憾\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Look, I'm very sorry about the governor,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.47,0:20:02.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,显然我也乐意挽救他的生命，但是…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}and I obviously would have loved to have saved his life too, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.06,0:20:05.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我是说，我在场，她在那里\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I mean, I was there and she was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.69,0:20:09.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道发生了什么，但现在州长死了…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}We know what happened, but the governor is dead now and...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.44,0:20:13.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们不想他的家庭蒙羞\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}...we don't want to embarrass his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.53,0:20:17.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你不知道，要是媒体知道这样的事，他们会干出什么来？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Do you have any idea what the press would do if they got ahold of a thing like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.41,0:20:20.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你要我做什么？说她不在场？我已经告诉警察了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What you want me do? To say she wasn't there? I already told the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.85,0:20:23.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那方面已经摆平了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's already taken care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.83,0:20:30.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 好吧，那女孩怎么办呢？  - 我会跟她谈，我肯定她会合作的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- All right. What about the girl? - I'll talk to her. I'm sure she's cooperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.17,0:20:35.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只不过是一个游伴，消失在麦克雷的车里，就那样？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Just one playmate just vanishes from McRyan's car, just like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.18,0:20:38.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 正确  - 老天，我不知道\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- That's right. - Aw, Jesus, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.51,0:20:40.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就不能闭上嘴吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Can't you keep your mouth shut?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.51,0:20:43.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,州长一个人死去会更好\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's better the governor died alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.06,0:20:48.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我就是不知道能不能做得到，我在场，她在场，还有…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I just don't know if I can do that. I was there, she was there, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.90,0:20:51.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有谁把你在场当回事？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Who gives a damn that you were there?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.78,0:20:55.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你要告诉他妻子，说他死时还跟某个女孩有染吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You wanna tell his wife that he died with his hand up some girl's dress?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.17,0:20:57.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许你想让她从报上读到？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Maybe your'd rarther she read it in the papers?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.10,0:21:00.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事情就是如此，那是真相，不是吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}That is what happened. That is the truth, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.40,0:21:04.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对你来说有什么区别？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What difference does that make to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.21,0:21:10.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但对他的家庭来说区别可就大了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}But it would make a great deal of difference to his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.01,0:21:18.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.93,0:21:22.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好，我们会让你和那女孩儿分头走后门出去\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Good. We'll slip you and the girl out the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.77,0:21:31.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你家如何？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}How about your place?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.19,0:21:33.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你不想回家，对吧？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You don't wanna go home, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.28,0:21:39.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他们跟你说了谁在车上，对吧？  - 对\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- They told you who was in the car, right? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.62,0:21:44.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗯，有些聪明的记者会想到我也在，知道吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, some smart reporter could figure I was there too, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.79,0:21:48.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们拿到我的包，有我的名字和地址\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}They got my purse with my name and address.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.04,0:21:51.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们会在我家门口扎营的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}They're gonna be camped on my doorstep.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.67,0:21:55.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那我家门口呢？我是救你出来的人，对吧？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What about my doorstep? I'm the one who pulled you out of that wreck, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.09,0:21:58.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是的，没错\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.40,0:22:00.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,咱们去找家汽车旅馆吧\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Let's go to a motel.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.06,0:22:07.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,先是喝一杯，然后是我家，现在是汽车旅馆\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}First it's a drink, then it's my place, now it's a motel.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.98,0:22:11.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,今晚事情发展很快，莎莉\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Things are movin' fast tonight, Sally.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.99,0:22:23.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哎哟\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Whoops.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.12,0:22:25.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,站这里等一会儿\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Stand here for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.90,0:23:38.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 美好的夜晚，适合散步  - 是的，没错\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- ...Beautiful night for a walk. - Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.57,0:23:41.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们沿着河边散步吧\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Let's take a walk along the river here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.16,0:23:45.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 呣，好  - 戴维，看\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Mm. Nice. - David, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.20,0:23:48.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 桥上有人  - 咱们别操这份心了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Someone's on the bridge. - Let's not worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.24,0:23:50.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他正盯着我们  - 谁管呢？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- He's staring right at us. - Who cares?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.54,0:23:52.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我管  - 贝琪\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I care. - Betsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.37,0:23:55.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我不想待在这里了，咱们走吧  - 好\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I don't wanna stay here anymore. Let's go. - Yeah, OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.46,0:23:57.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他在干什么？  - 我不知道\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- What is he doing? - I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.67,0:24:03.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他是什么人，偷窥者什么的？  - 哦，谁管呢？咱们从这边下去吧\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- What is he, a Peeping Tom or something? - Oh, who cares? Let's walk down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.29,0:25:13.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,老天爷\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.36,0:25:42.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,糟糕\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.86,0:27:53.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗯，你要咖啡吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}So, uh... you want some coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.83,0:27:59.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 喂，你要咖啡吗？  - 呣，早上好\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Huh? You want some coffee? - Mm. Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.95,0:28:02.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 嗨，你好吗？  - 我还好，你好吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Hi. How you doin'? - I'm fine. How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.37,0:28:05.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很好，给你\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Pretty good. There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.25,0:28:08.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在这里干嘛？你在听什么音乐吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What are you doin' here? You listenin' to some music?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.30,0:28:13.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不，这是…是我的工作\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Nope. This is my... This is my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.97,0:28:17.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我为电影做音效  - 哦，电影？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I do sound effects for movies. - Oh, movies, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.26,0:28:20.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上，昨晚我出去录一些音\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Matter of fact, last night I was out recording some sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.48,0:28:22.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,什么意思？音效？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What do you mean, sound effects?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.44,0:28:29.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你知道，你看电影的时候，听见关门或是鸟叫啊风声啊，不管什么\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, when you see a movie and you hear a door slam or a bird chirp or wind, or whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.28,0:28:31.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我录下那些真实声音\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I record those actual sounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.90,0:28:35.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后放进电影里，然后你就看到那部电影\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}and then I put them in a movie, and then you see the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.49,0:28:36.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 哦  - 昨晚…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Oh. - Last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.03,0:28:39.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 大制作？  - 不，只是…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Big movies? - No. Just...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.20,0:28:41.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只是些烂片，很不幸\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Just bad ones, unfortunately.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.70,0:28:43.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我真的喜欢电影\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I really love movies, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.00,0:28:48.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这对我来说是很有趣的题目，因为我是做化妆的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's a very interesting subject to me because I do make-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.52,0:28:49.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 是吗？  - 对\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}-Do you? -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.92,0:28:54.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,目前只是在柜台工作，但我梦想做电影化妆\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Right now it's only behind a counter, but I dream about doin' make-up for movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.68,0:28:59.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我见过大电影明星，比如芭芭拉·史翠珊，你知道吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I've seen these big movie stars like Barbra Streisand, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.42,0:29:01.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他们没给化好  - 对\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- They don't do it right. - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.82,0:29:05.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我知道如何修饰面部  - 真的吗？真不错\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I know how to fix a face. - Really? That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.97,0:29:08.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我要你听一些东西\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I want you to hear something. Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.54,0:29:14.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,昨晚我录音的时候，录下了你的事故\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Last night I was recording some sounds, and I recorded your accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.50,0:29:16.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,整个过程都录下来了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I got the whole thing on tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.54,0:29:19.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 哦，你录下了事故  - 对，录了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Oh. You recorded the accident. - Yes, I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.46,0:29:23.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过我认为那不是事故，我认为你们的车胎是被枪打爆的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Except I don't think you had an accident. I think your tyre was shot out.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.64,0:29:26.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 这太扯了  - 不，真的，听听这个\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- That's crazy. - No, it's not. Listen to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.80,0:29:29.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你会听到两声，第一下是枪声\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're gonna hear two sounds. The first is a gunshot
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.80,0:29:31.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第二下是爆胎声\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}and the second is a blowout.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.12,0:29:33.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,明白了吗？听着\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}All right? Listen up.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.90,0:29:46.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 再听一遍  - 我听到一个声音，我不知道，也许是枪声\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Now listen again. - I mean I heard a noise. I don't konw, maybe that was a gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.07,0:29:50.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过我跟你说实话，我不太想听昨晚的重播\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}But, I'll tell you the truth, I don't really feature listenin' to a replay of last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.62,0:29:52.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有些压抑\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's kinda depressing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.79,0:29:54.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我能问你点事吗？  - 什么？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Can I ask you something? - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.04,0:29:57.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你当时跟麦克雷在做什么？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What were you doing with McRyan?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.75,0:30:03.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 这个问题太私人了，不关你的事  - 不\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}-That's a very personal question. That's none of your business. -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.10,0:30:07.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我不是要细节，只是…  - 我要感冒了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I don't mean the details. I just... - I'm gettin' a cold here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.80,0:30:10.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 算了，莎莉  - 私人问题\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Forget it, Sally. - Personal questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.10,0:30:13.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,-  我都不知道你是谁  - 我很愿意让你知道我是谁\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I don't even know who you are. - I'd like you to get to know who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.30,0:30:16.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 还去喝一杯吗？  - 另找时间吧，好吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- How about that drink? - Some other time, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.56,0:30:21.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,莎莉，我救了你的命，至少你可以跟我喝一杯\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sally, I saved your life. The least you could do is have a drink with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.00,0:30:27.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧，你可以打电话到我朋友朱迪·黛敏那里找我，我会去那边\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}All right. You can call me at my girlfriend Judy Demming's. I'll be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.50,0:30:30.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 电话簿里有她  - 好吧，你跟我说的是实话？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- She's in the book. - All right. You tellin' me the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.48,0:30:34.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 是  - 好吧，我会给你打电话\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Yeah. - All right. I'm gonna call you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.16,0:30:35.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.11,0:30:55.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,（阿波罗成人电影售票中心  限制级电影整晚放映）
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.95,0:31:02.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,（独立电影公司）
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.40,0:31:07.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,杰克，他们拿到麦克雷死亡的影片，我刚在收音机听到的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jack. They got movies of McRyan gettin' killed. I just heard it on the radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.95,0:31:09.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 也许新闻上有  - 什么？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Maybe it's on the news. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.91,0:31:12.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,麦克雷死亡的影片\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Movies of McRyan gettin' killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.41,0:31:15.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,似乎难以置信，一位本地摄影师，曼尼·卡普\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Incredible as it may seem, a local photographer, Manny Karp,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.83,0:31:18.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,昨晚正在事故现场，带着摄像机\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}was on the scene of the accident last night, with his camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.75,0:31:24.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,“城市之眼”新闻获悉，卡普先生今早把他的影片卖给“今日新闻”杂志\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}'Eyes on the City' News has learnd that Mr Karp sold his film to 'News Today' magazine this morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.51,0:31:26.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 《今日新闻》…  - 嘘\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- News Today... - Shh.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.80,0:31:30.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的弗兰克·多纳休卡普先生谈过，就在不久前\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Our own Frank Donahue spoke with Mr Karp just a few moments ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.30,0:31:33.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就在杂志社办公室外\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}...outside the magazine's offices.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.43,0:31:37.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我跟你说，我出去试用新的电影胶片\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, I'll tell ya. I had gone out there to try out this new film stock, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.69,0:31:42.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常高速的胶片，适合夜间摄影，晚上我要干很多活\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's a very high speed. It's good for night shooting. I do a lotta work at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.98,0:31:48.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我正在站那里，突然之间我听见有车沿着道路开来\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}So anyway I'm standing out there and all of a sudden I hear this car barrellin' down the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.65,0:31:53.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我没太注意，突然之间我听见它在打滑\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I didn't pay too much attention till all of a sudden I hear it startin' to skid.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.20,0:31:57.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想都没想，转过身，我的摄影机在转，我捕捉到了他冲出栏杆\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I wasn't even think of it. I just turn around, my camera's runnin' and I catch him goin' through the railing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.00,0:32:01.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡普先生，弗兰克·唐纳休，“城市之眼”新闻\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mr Karp. Frank Donahue, 'Eye on the City' News.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.42,0:32:04.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡普先生，州长是如何驾驶的？他在控制车辆吗\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mr Karp, was the governor driving? Was he in control?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.34,0:32:07.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,控制？它冲进河里了，他没有控制\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Control? It went into the drink. He wasn't in no control.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.47,0:32:10.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他是一个人在车里吗？  - 我没看见什么人\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Was he alone in the car? - I didn't see anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.34,0:32:14.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你为何没找警察？  - 不不，不不\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Why didn't you go to the police? - Oh, no. No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.10,0:32:17.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 警察从没对我好过  - 嗨，杰克\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- No cop ever did anything for me. - Hey, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.10,0:32:19.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们不会像这里的人一样给我钱\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}They ain't gonna give me money like these guys here given me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.94,0:32:21.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你去哪儿？  - 我得走了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Where you goin'? - I gotta go.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.77,0:32:24.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你要走？试片怎么办？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You gotta go? What about the auditions?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.98,0:32:27.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,独家照片，麦克雷之死\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Exclusive photos. McRyan's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.99,0:32:32.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,请一个一个来，独家照片，麦克雷之死\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}One at a time, please. Exclusive photos. McRyan's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.08,0:32:35.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 快到时间了  - 里克在吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- It's about time. - Is Rick in?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.74,0:32:39.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 不在，不过萨姆带着女孩们来给你听  - 把他钥匙给我，快点快点\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- No. But Sam's got girls for you to hear. - Give me his key. Come on, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.00,0:32:43.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 萨姆和女孩们怎么办？  - 我回头再办\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- What about Sam and the girls? - I'll do it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.30,0:33:01.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,杰克？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jack?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.94,0:33:03.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喂，杰克\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yo, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.65,0:33:07.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开门，我是萨姆\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Come on, open up. It's Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.15,0:33:09.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,杰克\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.70,0:33:28.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,（麦克雷之爆胎悲剧）
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.28,0:35:22.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是影片的关键时刻，你们得了解\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}This is the pivotal moment in the film. You gotta realise that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.70,0:35:25.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 杰克，你他妈去哪儿？  - 萨姆，我很快就回\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Jack. Where the fuck are you goin'? - Sam, I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.79,0:35:28.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我现在需要你，快进来\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I need you now. Now get in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.75,0:35:34.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你觉得怎样？  - 继续找\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- What do you think? - Keep lookin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.92,0:35:37.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,继续找？嗨，杰克，你说什么呢？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Keep lookin'? Hey, Jack. What're you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.02,0:35:53.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉，杰克，我时间占满了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sorry, Jack. I'm all stacked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.52,0:35:56.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拜托，就这一次，就当帮我个忙，好吗\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Please, just this once, as a favour to me. All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.20,0:36:00.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我试试看吧，午夜回来找我\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'll see what I can do. Come back after midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.95,0:36:02.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,莎莉？我是杰克\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sally? It's Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.42,0:36:05.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,瞧，我说过我会给你打电话\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}See? I told you I'd call you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.00,0:36:07.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你答应过的，喝一杯如何？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}How about that drink you promised?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.67,0:36:13.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你去哪儿？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Where are you goin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.59,0:36:18.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要不我去车站见你好了？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why don't I meet you at the station?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.97,0:36:28.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,莎莉\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sally.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.73,0:36:30.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗨\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.19,0:36:34.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 真高兴逮到你了  - 对，我要出门\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I'm so glad I caught you. - Yeah, I was out the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.77,0:36:36.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,听好，我只有20分钟\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Look, I only got 20 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.69,0:36:39.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没事，我们赶快喝，然后你走你的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's fine. We'll have a quick drink and you'll be on your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.42,0:36:43.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是…我想抢个好座位，你知道的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well... I wanna get a good seat, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.28,0:36:45.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,得了，莎莉，你答应过我的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Aw, come on, Sally. You promised me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.60,0:36:47.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧，但只有10分钟\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}OK, but just 10 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.37,0:36:51.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 好，来，我来拿  - 好，谢谢\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- OK. Come on. Let me take this. - OK. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.29,0:36:53.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你感觉如何？  - 很好\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- How are you feelin'? - Pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.32,0:36:54.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你看起来不错  - 谢谢\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You look nice. - Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.77,0:36:57.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,纽约、莱港、斯坦福、纽黑文\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.98,0:37:00.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,新伦敦、普罗维丹斯和波士顿\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.18,0:37:03.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,三号月台\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.22,0:37:09.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你见人的时候，第一眼看的是什么？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What's the first thing you see when you meet somebody?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.77,0:37:12.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,双腿，我是喜欢腿的人\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Legs. I'm a leg man.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.27,0:37:17.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 得了  - 好吧，脸，先看脸\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Come on. - All right. Face. You see their face.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.15,0:37:18.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正确\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.78,0:37:25.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以，要是你的脸不合适，没人会想再见到你\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}So, if your face doesn't look right, no one is gonna look at you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.32,0:37:29.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我认为你的脸不需要化妆  - 每张脸都需要化妆\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I don't think your face needs make-up. - Every face needs make-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.37,0:37:31.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 但不能看出化了妆  - 哦，我明白了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- But it shouldn't look like make-up. - Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.00,0:37:37.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我这张脸修饰过，我隐藏了一切，所以你看不出化妆\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I've worked on this face. I've hidden everything so you don't see the make-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.67,0:37:40.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你现在化了妆？  - 对，化了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You got make-up on right now? - Yeah, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.59,0:37:44.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我不相信，我不相信   - 肯定的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I don't believe it. I don't believe it. - Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.47,0:37:48.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你看，这花了我两个小时，这就是“无化妆面容”\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}And, you see, this took me two hours. And this is the 'no make-up look'.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.97,0:37:53.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真的？我倒想看看“有化妆面容”是什么样，肯定很漂亮，对吧\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Really? I'd like to see what the 'make-up look' looks like. I bet that's good, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.39,0:37:57.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我…我只在特殊场合化那种\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, I... I only do that for special occasions.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.19,0:38:00.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,断过的鼻子怎么办？你怎么处理呢？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}How about a broken nose? How would you deal with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.28,0:38:03.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦，这个容易，你只要用一点…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, that's easy. You just take a little...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.49,0:38:06.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等等，我看一下，我可以给你看\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Wait a minute. Let me see. I can show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.37,0:38:09.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对，你拿一支这样的刷子\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah. You get a brush like this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.91,0:38:12.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你弄一点棕色粉\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You take a little brown powder.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.41,0:38:14.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你只要刷一点棕色…  - 你在干吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You just make a little brown... - What are you doin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.53,0:38:18.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嘿，等一下，这可是很认真的工作\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, wait a minute. This is serious business here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.54,0:38:21.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你有没有兴趣？  - 有有，对不起\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You interested or not? - Oh, yes. OK. Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.46,0:38:23.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你弄一条棕色线，要晕染出来，就在这里\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You make a brown line and kinda smudge it in right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.05,0:38:27.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要相当微妙，不让人察觉\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It has to be real subtle so as no one'll notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.85,0:38:30.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过…你笑什么？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}But... What are you smiling about?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.06,0:38:34.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我很佩服你了解这么多\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm impressed that you know so much about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.23,0:38:36.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你根本不感兴趣  - 不，我有\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You're not interested at all. - Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.85,0:38:40.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你没有，你只是让我坐在这里不停说话，好让我错过火车\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're not. You just kept me sittin' here talkin' so I'd miss my train.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.57,0:38:43.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这不是真的，莎莉，我只是不想你走\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's not true, Sally. I just didn't want you to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.74,0:38:44.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.86,0:38:48.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为我喜欢你，我才遇见你而你又要离开我了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Because I like you, and I just met you and you're goin' off on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.28,0:38:50.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道，我对你一无所知\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I don't know. I don't know anything about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.46,0:38:53.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你想知道什么？你想知道的我都会告诉你\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What do you wanna know? I'll tell you anything you wanna know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.66,0:38:57.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 好吧，你是个音效师，对吧？  - 对\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- All right. You're a sound man, right? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.96,0:39:00.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好，你怎么得到这份工作的？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}OK. How'd you get that job?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.25,0:39:03.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好问题，我不知道\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's a good question. I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.14,0:39:11.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我是那种孩子，修收音机，自己弄立体声\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I was the kind of kid who fixed radios, made my own stereos,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.60,0:39:14.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,什么科学竞赛都赢，你知道这种人\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}won all the science fairs - you know the type.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.32,0:39:18.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,之后我服役了，进了军队，在那里精进了技能\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}After that I went into the service, I went into the army, and I refined my skills there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.56,0:39:21.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦，是吗？你参加过什么战争吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, yeah? Were you in any wars or anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.44,0:39:25.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有，我是通讯奇才，他们不愿让我离开新泽西\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}No, no. I was such a communication whiz, they wouldn't let me leave New Jersey.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.82,0:39:31.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,后来我去警察部门待过一段，那之后去了电影业\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Then I went into the police for a while, and after that I went into movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.12,0:39:33.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等一下，你当过警察？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Wait a minute. You were a cop?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.54,0:39:36.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 不，我为基恩委员会工作  - 那是什么？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- No. I worked for the Kean Commission. - What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.71,0:39:40.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些政客聚在一起，想要阻止警察腐败\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}A group of politicians that got together to try to stop police corruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.88,0:39:43.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 哦  - 后来我退出了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Oh. - Then I quit that and...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.80,0:39:45.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你做了什么？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, what'd you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.01,0:39:48.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,说来话长，你不会想知道的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's a long story. You don't wanna know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.21,0:39:52.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想，我真的想，这很有趣\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, I do. I really do. This is very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.98,0:39:55.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,电影呢？你不是想听电影的事吗\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}How about movies? I thought you wanted to know about movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.31,0:39:57.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对，电影很棒，但这…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, movies are great, but this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.11,0:40:00.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就像是街头的真实生活，知道吗\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}this is like real life on the streets. You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.73,0:40:02.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很刺激\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.61,0:40:06.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.78,0:40:09.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我…我给他们最好的卧底警察连线\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I, um... I wired their best undercover cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.08,0:40:12.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个化名费雷迪·科尔索的人\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}A guy by the name of Freddie Corso.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.62,0:40:16.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,弗雷迪有个案子，是给一个腐败警监下套\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}And one of Freddie's cases was to set up a corrupt police captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.33,0:40:18.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那人正要勒索一个黑帮分子\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}...who was tryin' to shake down a Mob guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.62,0:40:22.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我的工作是给他连线以便记录对话\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}And my job was to rig a wire on him so I could record the conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.57,0:40:25.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等一下，“连线”是什么意思？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Wait a minute. What do you mean, 'wire'?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.25,0:40:30.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是个微型麦克风，连在我拴在弗雷迪腰间的发射器上\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's a tiny mike attached to a transmitter that I strapped around Freddie's waist.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.72,0:40:36.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,麦基，把录音带递给我\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mackey, hand me the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.77,0:40:43.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 好了，弗雷迪，检查声音，数到10  - 一、二、三、四…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- OK, Freddie, give me sound. Count to 10. - One, two, three, four, five...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.32,0:40:53.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,窃听器很棒，他可能会被阻挡\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It was a great wire. He could be blocks away...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.28,0:40:56.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但你可以听到他10英尺范围内一切声音，很妙\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}...and you could hear everything within 10 feet of him. It's fantastic
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.45,0:40:59.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 嘿，米尔特，你好吗？  - 你好，弗雷迪，你好\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Hey, Milt. How ya doin'? - Hello, Freddie. How ya doin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.54,0:41:02.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 很高兴见到你  - 你气色不错\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Good to see ya. - You look good.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.38,0:41:05.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你也是，你这身装扮不错  - 谢谢\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Yes, so are you. You look great in that get-up. - Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.13,0:41:09.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我带了个人来见你\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}So, uh... I brought somebody here I want you to meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.59,0:41:11.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,肯尼迪警监，这是米尔特\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Captain Kennedy, this is Milt.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.76,0:41:13.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谁他妈想见肯尼迪警监了？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Who the fuck wants to meet Captain Kennedy?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.05,0:41:18.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 米尔特，放松  - 嘿，我不想见他\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Milt, take it easy. - Hey, I don't wanna meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.31,0:41:22.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嘿，放轻松，这人能调动警察，你可就方便了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, take it easy. This man could put the cap on everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.52,0:41:26.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好了，上车来，我们边兜风边聊\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}All right, come on in the car. We'll take a ride and talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.15,0:41:29.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那个警监跟那个黑帮分子说的第一件事\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}And the first thing that the captain says to the Mob guy:
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.78,0:41:33.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,瞧，我知道这人有个妹夫\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Look, I understand that the man has a brother-in-law.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.16,0:41:36.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我碰巧看见他跟他妹夫说话\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now, I happened to see him alkin' to his brother-in-law.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.41,0:41:39.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个妹夫是个重罪犯，弗雷迪\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now, the brother-in-law is a known felon, Freddie,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.29,0:41:42.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,米尔特正在假释期间，这是违反假释条例的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}and Milt's out on parole, and that's a parole violation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.87,0:41:45.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这事我得告诉假释官，明白吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now, I'm gonna have to tell the parole officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.87,0:41:48.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要是我告诉假释官，他就得回监狱去\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}If I tell the parole officer, he's goin' back in the can.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.92,0:41:54.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过我觉得我能想点办法，不告诉他，给5千块就行\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}But I think I could work somethin' out that I don't have to tell him for... 5,000 bucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.43,0:42:00.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,5千？弗雷迪，你这小狗日的，我们开始说是1千的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}$5,000? Freddie, you little prick. We started this thing for $1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.60,0:42:02.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1千？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}$1,000?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.10,0:42:06.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些我录得很清楚，然后我就听到了静电干扰\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm gettin' this clear as a bell on tape and I start to hear the static.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.40,0:42:11.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你认为可以？你脑袋坏了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You think you can? You're outta your.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.11,0:42:12.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,咱们可以处理好的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}We can work this thing out.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.21,0:42:24.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他要进监狱的，你明白吗？  - 对\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- He's goin' up the river. You understand? - Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.00,0:42:26.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,怎么回事？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.80,0:42:28.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在流汗，弗雷迪，怎么回事？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're sweatin', Freddie. What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.05,0:42:34.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有件事那个他妈的神童没想到，弗雷迪会紧张流汗\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}The one thing that fuckin' whiz kid didn't figure Freddie would get nervous and sweat.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.53,0:42:38.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他流汗太多，发射器里的电池短路了，在他身上烧了个洞\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}He sweated so bad that the battery in the transmitter shorted out and burned a hole in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.68,0:42:41.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嘿，在这加油站停一下，我要撒尿\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, pull over to this gas station. I gotta take a piss.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.87,0:43:08.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 糟糕  - 怎么了，杰克？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Shit. - What's wrong, Jack?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.33,0:43:10.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 电池在漏电  - 电池在漏电？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}-The battery is arcing. -The battery is arcing?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.12,0:43:13.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发射器里的电池在漏电，正在灼伤他，我得进去\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}The battery in the transmitter is arcing. It's burning him. I gotta get in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.21,0:43:16.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你不能去，你会暴露他的  - 我必须进去\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You can't. You'll blow the guy's cover. - I gotta go in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.25,0:43:19.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你不能去  - 我那块他妈的电池正在灼伤他\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You can't. - My fuckin' battery burned a hole in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.01,0:43:21.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 这我不管，你会搞砸这行动的  - 嘘\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I don't give a damn. You're gonna screw things up. - Shh.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.14,0:43:26.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我得去  - 杰克，你疯了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I gotta go. - Jack, you're nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.00,0:43:48.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,老天爷\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Aw, Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.00,0:43:51.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,啊  不\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Aw... no.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.61,0:44:17.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这不是你的错\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It wasn't your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.81,0:44:19.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是啊，你跟弗雷迪说去\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, well, you tell that to Freddie.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.07,0:44:20.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,妈的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Shit
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.70,0:44:22.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你没事吧\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Are you OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.95,0:44:28.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有事，有件事困扰我，那个亨利的事，州长的助理\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}No. Something's buggin' me. This whole thing with Henry, the governor's assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.23,0:44:29.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦，他也跟你谈过了？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, he talked to you too, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.60,0:44:32.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我就是为此要离城的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's why I'm leavin' town.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.71,0:44:35.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他给了我一些钱，让我消失一阵子\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}He gave me some money to disappear for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.34,0:44:36.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想也是，听着\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I thought so. Look,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.04,0:44:39.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们要掩盖的事远不是你跟麦克雷在一起\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}they are covering up a lot more than you being with McRyan.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.84,0:44:41.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我知道轮胎不是爆胎\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I know that tyre was shot out.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.84,0:44:43.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么这么肯定？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}How can you be so sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.68,0:44:46.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你看过《今日新闻》杂志吗？  - 看过\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Did you see the News Today magazine? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.01,0:44:47.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,照片\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Photos
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.13,0:44:49.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想了个办法，把我录的声音配在那些照片上\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I figure out a way to put my sound with those photographs.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.71,0:44:52.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等你看了，我肯定你就知道那不是爆胎\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}And when you see it, I'm sure you'll see it was no blowout.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.02,0:44:56.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.61,0:44:59.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你能帮我个忙吗？可以多留几天吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Would you do me favour? Would you stick around for a couple of days?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.57,0:45:02.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 为了什么？  - 我只是觉得这事你可以帮我忙\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- What for? - I just think you could help me with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.32,0:45:09.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,杰克，我不知道，我已经惹了很多麻烦了，要是我留在这里…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jack, I don't know. I'm in a helluva lot of trouble already. If I stick around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.16,0:45:11.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只要我能为自己理清这里的事情…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}If I can just clear myself of this...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.71,0:45:14.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,咱们可以一起走，我是说…有何不可？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}We could go away together. I mean... why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.92,0:45:17.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你自己走又有什么意思呢？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What the hell's the sense of goin' away by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.90,0:45:21.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我不知道  - 求你了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I don't know. - Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.97,0:45:31.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我得想一想什么的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I have to think about it or somethin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.23,0:45:37.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我得想想\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'll think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.35,0:48:18.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,（自由日庆典）
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.35,0:49:39.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嘿，莎莉，近来可好？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, Sal. How ya doin', huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.77,0:49:43.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很高兴见到…我就是转转，看看电视里这部好看的电影\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's good to see... I was just hangin' around, watchin' this great movie on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.02,0:49:46.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你气色好极了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You look terrific.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.69,0:49:50.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对啊，你在雷丁做些什么呢？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah. So what are you doin' in Reading?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.32,0:49:57.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,听着，你想喝点什么吗？来点威士忌怎么样？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Listen, you want somethin' to drink here? How about some Scotch?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.38,0:50:09.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 喂  - 是莎莉\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Yeah? - It's Sally.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.13,0:50:16.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嘿，莎莉，进来进来\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, Sal. Hey, come on in. Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.35,0:50:19.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你气色真好，你来做什么呢？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You look great. What are you doin' around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.10,0:50:21.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天，曼尼，他们不打扫这地方吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jesus, Manny. Don't they ever clean this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.33,0:50:26.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对啊，得早起才能碰见女佣，我还没早起过\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You gotta get up real early to catch a maid. I haven't made it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.90,0:50:30.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我真高兴你能过来，知道吗\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, I'm sure glad you come by, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.32,0:50:32.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,听着，你怎么找到我的？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Listen, how'd you find me?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.90,0:50:35.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,算了吧，曼尼，我们来这里工作无数回了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Come on, Manny. We worked this place a million times.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.04,0:50:38.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦，对哦，你想喝点吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, yeah, that's right. Hey, you want a drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.33,0:50:41.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 这回不是社交拜访，曼尼  - 哦，不是吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- This isn't a social visit, Manny. - Oh, no, huh? Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.87,0:50:43.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那晚上你差点害死我了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You almost got me killed the other night.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.27,0:50:45.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,害死我，你明白吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Dead-- you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.75,0:50:49.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦，宝贝，我跟那事没关系，那是个意外\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, hey, babe. I didn't have nothin' to do with that. That was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.13,0:50:50.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 是吗？  - 对啊\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Yeah? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.49,0:50:53.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你怎么回事？  - 什么意思，我怎么回事？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- What happened to you? - What do you mean what happened to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.80,0:50:57.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我一看见那小子跳进河里就溜了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I took off as soon as I saw that kid jump into the creek.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.51,0:51:01.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他干得可比我好太多了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}He did a helluva lot better job than I coulda ever done.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.68,0:51:05.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你瞧，我不知道以前是不是跟你说过…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know, I don't know if I ever told you this before but...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.48,0:51:08.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我连游泳都不会，宝贝\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I can't even swim, babe.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.23,0:53:54.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太好了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.62,0:54:58.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,泰瑞，你知道今天我这里来过多少说阴谋论的疯子吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Terry, do you know how many conspiracy nuts I've already had in here today?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.80,0:54:59.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不知道\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.92,0:55:02.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要是他们每个人都他妈给我一角钱\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}If I had a fuckin' dime for every god damn one of 'em
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.52,0:55:05.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我就可以买下整个佛罗里达州，平安退休了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'd buy the whole state of Florida and retire in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.05,0:55:08.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些照片里很清晰，闪光和烟\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's very clear in all these photos. The flash and the smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.14,0:55:09.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有好多种可能，这并不代表什么\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It could be a lot of things. They don't mean nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.30,0:55:13.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么样样事都他妈得有阴谋？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why the fuck does everything have to be a conspiracy?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.14,0:55:17.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个人喝多了几杯，他开出道路，掉进河里\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}A man has a couple too many drinks, he drives off the road, falls into a creek.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.69,0:55:20.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 意外事故，简单明了  - 这不是意外\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Accident, plain and simple. - It was not an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.13,0:55:21.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,听着，我来告诉你\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Look, let me tell you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.28,0:55:24.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我在场，轮胎被射爆，我听见了，我记录下来了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I was there. That tyre was shot out. I heard it. I recorded it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.61,0:55:28.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以你是一场刺杀的耳听证人喽，太好了，真动听\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}So you're an earwitness to an assassination. That's great. It's got a nice ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.99,0:55:32.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 是你牵头调查吗？  - 对\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Are you heading up the investigation? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.66,0:55:36.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你检查过麦克雷的轮胎吗？  - 没，干嘛查？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Did you check McRyan's tyre? - No. Why should I?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.12,0:55:38.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为会有子弹洞眼，因为他是被杀的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Because there's a bullet hole in there. Because he was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.33,0:55:41.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 就你这么说，泰瑞，别人都说是意外  - 谁？谁说是意外？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Says you, Terry. Everybody else says accident. - Who? Who says accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.55,0:55:45.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我这有一整套特别委员会的报告，会说是意外\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I got a whole special commission formin' here that's gonna say it was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.68,0:55:47.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,报告会说是意外？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's gonna say it was an accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.30,0:55:48.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,得了，他们没有证据\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Come on. They have no evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.70,0:55:51.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们没有录音带、轮胎，他们没跟我谈过\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}They don't have the tape, the tyre, they didn't speak to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.45,0:55:55.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你和你他妈的录音带我全知道，你害了很多好警察\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I know all about you and your fuckin' tapes. You put a lotta good cops away.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.02,0:55:59.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那跟这事一点关系都没有，那是职务行为，而且我恨它\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}That has nothin' to do with this, that's a position, and I resent it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.77,0:56:02.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我认为你名声太臭，做这种事就会这样\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think you stink. That's what it's got to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.61,0:56:06.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嘿，你，我不喜欢你并不意味着我不会做好本职\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Hey, you. Just because I don't like you does not mean I'm not gonna do my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.95,0:56:10.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把带子给我，我会送到实验室，让人检查\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Now gimme that tape. I'll send it over to the lab and I'll have it checked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.91,0:56:16.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好了，我要你看看我用那些照片做的片子，你会明白的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}All right, look, I want you to look at that film I made from those photos. I think you'll get the idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.29,0:56:20.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要是我们能拿到卡普的原片，枪击会清楚得多\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}But if we can get Karp's original film, this gunshot'll be a lot clearer.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.17,0:56:23.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡普把他的片子成捆卖给一家有一家杂志社\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Karp is makin' a bundle sellin' his pictures from one magazine to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.01,0:56:26.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你凭什么认为他会给我们？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What the hell makes you think he's gonna give 'em to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.67,0:56:29.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他必须如此，那是证据   - 我找不到他，泰瑞\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- He's got to. It's evidence. - I can't find him, Terry.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.88,0:56:33.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 找到他，这是你的工作  - 别对我的工作指手画脚\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Find him. It's your job, man. - Don't tell me how to do my goddam job.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.23,0:56:34.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,知道吗，他可以回答几个问题\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know he could answer us some questions
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.74,0:56:36.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如他他妈的带着摄像机去那儿到底干嘛\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}like what the fuck he was really doin' with his camera up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.93,0:56:39.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没人想知道，没人在乎\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Nobody wants to know. Nobody cares.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.35,0:56:43.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有肮脏的细节，没有政治暗杀，是意外\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}No sordid details. No political assassination. Accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.11,0:56:44.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,老天在上这人已经死了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}This guy's dead for crise sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.84,0:56:46.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些东西对他没什么好处了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}None of this shit's gonna do him any good now.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.53,0:56:48.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这不是为了他，我知道他已经死了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}This isn't for him. I know he's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.14,0:56:53.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你不明白吗？要是他们杀了麦克雷又逃脱法网，下一个会杀谁？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Don't you understand? If they can get away with killing McRyan, who's next?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.58,0:56:56.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,“他们”是谁？我要你先告诉我“他们”是谁？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Who's 'they'? First I want you to tell me who 'they' is.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.45,0:56:58.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那算什么？某种共产主义阴谋？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What is that? A communist conspiracy of some kind?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.82,0:57:02.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,又或是街上的什叶派教徒，拿着吹箭筒\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Or maybe it's couple of ayatollahs out of here in the street with blowguns.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.05,0:57:05.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 哦，你省省吧  - 留着你的妄想症上电视说吧\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Oh, give me a break. - Save your paranoia for public TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.55,0:57:07.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,去你的，马克，我要走了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Fuck you, Mac. I'm getting out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.11,0:57:08.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,放下那东西\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Put that stuff down.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.11,0:57:10.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,放下那些照片，否则我以扣留证物叫人逮捕你\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Put those pictures down, or I'll have you arrested for withholding evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.60,0:57:14.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.61,0:57:15.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.61,0:57:18.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我整天都在办公室，你能在那儿找到我\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'll be at the office all day. You can get me there.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.74,0:57:21.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我会打给你，别打给我\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'll call you. Don't call me.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.30,0:57:30.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我是布尔克，先生  - 什么？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- It's Burke, sir.  - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.35,0:57:33.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我是布尔克，先生\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}It's Burke, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.26,0:57:37.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 布尔克，你干了什么？  - 我不懂这问题，先生？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Burke. What have you done? - I don't understand the question, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.60,0:57:41.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你疯了吗？你只需要拿他的几张照片\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Are you crazy? You were just supposed to get some pictures of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.25,0:57:43.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你知道自己在说什么吗，先生？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Are you aware of what you're saying, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.75,0:57:44.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在哪里\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.96,0:57:50.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我在一个安全的电话亭打，我建议你给我打回来\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm calling from a secure phone booth. I suggest you call me back on same.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.05,0:58:18.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,打扰了，卡普先生在吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Excuse me. Is Mr Karp in?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.87,0:58:20.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我能进去吗？  - 干什么？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Could I go in? - What for?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.66,0:58:23.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我只是来拿几张照片  - 你是什么人？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I just have to pick up some pictures. - Are you anybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.61,0:58:28.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我是他的一个顾客  - 你知道，他有很多顾客\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I'm one of his customers. - You know, he had a lotta customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.16,0:58:30.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你是记者，对吧？  - 不是\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- You're a reporter, ain't ya? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.04,0:58:31.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你想要一份卡普的片子，对吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You want to get a piece of Karp's film, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.04,0:58:33.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道你在说什么\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I don't know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.63,0:58:36.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太糟了，没有法律禁止说谎，否则我今天就发了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Too bad there wasn't a law against lyin', I'd have made a lotta collars today
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.93,0:58:37.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,顾客先生\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Mr Customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.75,0:58:41.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我的确是顾客，我想拿我的照片   - 对，他也是顾客\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I am a customer and I'd like to pick up my pictures. - Yeah, he's a customer too.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.52,0:58:45.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他给我出价一千块  - 真的？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- He offered me a thousand bucks. - Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.31,0:58:47.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他妻子出价3千\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}And his wife offered me three.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.98,0:58:50.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看起来不值啊，但我估计你得在照片里才行\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Doesn't seem worth it but I guess you had to be there, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.00,0:58:54.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 看起来卡普做了一些离婚方面的工作  - 对\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}-Looks like Karp did a little divorce work on the side. -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.41,0:58:58.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对他的顾客毫不在意 我在他床底下找到一堆这个\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sure didn't give a shit about his customers. I found these in a heap under his bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.00,0:59:00.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是一些婴儿照\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's some baby picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.10,0:59:04.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你本该去弄到麦克雷的照片，不是杀了他\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You were supposed to get pictures of McRyan, not kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.37,0:59:07.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我了解行动目标，我从未同意过\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I understood the objectives of the operation. I never concured with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.88,0:59:10.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但我没有杀他，我是说，那是个意外\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}But I didn't kill him. I mean, it was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.10,0:59:13.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你意外射爆了他的轮胎？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You accidentally shot out the tyre of his car?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.88,0:59:17.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你也许能想起来，那是我在6月6日会面时提出的计划\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}As you may recall, this was my plan as proposed at our meeting of June 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.94,0:59:20.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们否决了那个计划，你不记得了吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}We rejected that plan. Don't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.89,0:59:24.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我当然记得，但我不得不越过我的权责界限\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Of cause I do. But I had to exceed the parameters of my authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.14,0:59:26.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但我的错误在误差范围内\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}But I stayed within an acceptable margin of error.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.02,0:59:31.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,毕竟，目标达成了，他被排除于选举之外\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}After all, the objective was achieved. He was eliminated from the election.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.53,0:59:36.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,布尔克，我不认识你，我从未见过你\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Burke, I don't know you. I've never seen you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.41,0:59:40.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 电话也别再给我打了  - 就一会儿，先生，有些残局我们还得收拾\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Don't ever call me again. - Just a minute sir. We got some loose ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.04,0:59:43.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我改了轮胎，让它看来像是爆胎\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I changed the tyre made it looked like a blowout.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.58,0:59:46.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我洗掉了那个音效师的带子，这样大家会认为他是个妄想家\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I erased the sound guy's tapes so everbody'll think he's a crackpot.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.82,0:59:49.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡普不见了，不过我会找到他\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Karp's disappeared, but I'll find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.46,0:59:51.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但还有那个女孩\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}But that still leaves the girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.90,0:59:56.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我已决定终结她，做成那地区系列色情杀手的样子\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I've decided to terminate her and make it look like one of a series of sex killings in the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.83,1:00:00.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 这样就完成了咱们行动的保护  - 什么行动？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- This would complete secure our operation. - What operation?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.50,1:00:08.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,快啊，贝蒂，再来一遍\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Come on, Betty. Try again.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.46,1:00:11.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第28次\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Take 28.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.09,1:00:16.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,停\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Cut.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.80,1:00:17.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,停\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Cut.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.80,1:00:19.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你得对着麦克风说，他们听不见\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You have to speak into the mike. They can't hear.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.80,1:00:21.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦，老天，停！\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh, Christ. Cut.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.90,1:00:26.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好了…交换\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}All right, uh... switch.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.83,1:00:29.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,贝蒂，你拉头发，珍，你来叫\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Betty, you pull the hair. Jean, you scream.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.69,1:00:32.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第29次\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Take 29.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.87,1:00:47.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 萨姆，我会在我房间里  - 嘿，你他妈去哪儿了？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Sam. I'll be in my room. - Hey. Where the fuck have you been?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.09,1:00:50.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我有些事情要办，好吧？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I had some business to take care of. All right?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.51,1:00:52.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,闭嘴\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.13,1:00:55.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你不是为我工作的吗？  - 是啊，有问题吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- I thought you were workin' for me. - I am. What's the problem?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.47,1:00:59.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们得给另一卷加音效，我们列了张表，记得吗？  - 好，我会弄的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- We need the effects for the other reel. We made a list for the scream, remember? - All right. Fine. I'll get 'em.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.31,1:01:01.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你会弄？我连第一卷的尖叫都没录上呢\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You'll get 'em? I haven't even got the scream for the first reel.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.06,1:01:03.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.96,1:02:58.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么不接电话？是警察\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why don't you answer your phone? It's the police.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.67,1:03:01.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 今天谁来过？  - 有个人，说是…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Who's been in here today? - Some guy, he said...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.18,1:03:04.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 谁？什么人？  - 我不喜欢你说话的语气\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Who? What guy? - I don't think I like your tone of voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.39,1:03:11.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 喂？  - 你搞什么鬼？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Yes? - What the hell is the matter with you?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.56,1:03:15.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 什么？  - 你他妈的带子上什么都没有\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- What? - Your fuckin' tape had nothin' on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.32,1:03:17.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我的带子全空了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}All my tapes are blank.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.10,1:03:20.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我搞不懂你了，首先你给我灌输了一堆暗杀什么的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You know I don't get you. First you feed me all this nutty assassination shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.03,1:03:23.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后你给我一卷空白带子，干嘛？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Then you give me a blank tape. What for?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.20,1:03:26.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为有人洗掉了，他们洗掉了我全部带子\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Because somebody erased it. They've erased all my tapes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.41,1:03:29.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦哦，对，“他们”，他们洗掉了你的带子\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Oh. Oh, yeah. 'They' - they erased your tapes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.75,1:03:33.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,下一步他们要做的就是去杀你？你他妈的神经\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What're they gonna be do is tryin' to kill you next? You're fuckin' nuts.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.17,1:03:42.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,莎莉？我是杰克\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Sally? It's Jack.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.59,1:03:46.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,听我说，我得给你看我做的那个片子\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Listen to me. I have to show you that film that I made.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.43,1:03:48.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,待在那边，我这就过去\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}So just stay there. I'm coming right over.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.57,1:04:01.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 杰克·泰瑞在吗？ - 在\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Is Jack Terry here? - Sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.65,1:04:03.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 弗兰克·唐纳休，第…  - 黛比\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Frank Donahue. Channel... - Debby.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.16,1:04:06.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 等等，他来了  - 杰克\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Wait a minute. There he is now. - Jack.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.51,1:04:08.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你好，我是弗兰克·唐纳休\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}How are you? I'm Frank Donahue.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.91,1:04:11.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 城市之眼新闻   - 哦，对对\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Eye on the City News. - Oh, yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.87,1:04:14.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我能跟你聊几分钟吗？  - 不，现在不行\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Could I talk to you a couple of minutes? - No. Not right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.33,1:04:18.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,得了，杰克，只要两分钟，我大老远过来，就两分钟\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Come on. Two minutes. That's all I need. I came all the way here. Two minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.88,1:04:21.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你想聊什么？  - 这事有些私密\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- What do you wanna talk about? - It's sort of private.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.88,1:04:23.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,咱们能进去说吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Can we go back here and talk?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.00,1:04:26.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 噢，好  - 太好了\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Uh... yeah.  - Great, great.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.51,1:04:29.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在这里制作电影啊？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}So you make movies here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.51,1:04:32.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我自认是个失败的演员，杰克\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think I'm a frustrated actor myself, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.27,1:04:33.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你想要什么\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.06,1:04:38.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你告诉警方有人枪击了麦克雷的车\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You told the police that someone shot out the tyre on McRyan's car.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.61,1:04:42.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 谁告诉你的？谁告诉你的？  - 杰克，这不重要\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Who told you that? Who told you? - Jack, that's not important.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.15,1:04:45.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我是记者，我有消息来源\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I'm a reporter. I've got my sources.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.28,1:04:49.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你这种人干嘛对我这样的暗杀妄想狂有兴趣？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Why would a guy like you be interested in some kind of assassination nut like me?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.79,1:04:51.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,杰克，我不认为…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Jack, I don't think...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.95,1:04:56.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 咱们能进去谈吗？  - 不不，这边\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Can we talk in here?  - No. No, no, no. Over here.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.80,1:05:01.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你说妄想狂是什么意思？我…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What do you mean, a nut? I...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.97,1:05:04.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不认为你是妄想狂，所以我才来\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I don't think you're a nut. In fact, that's why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.88,1:05:08.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我自己查探过这件事，好多事情都完全兜不拢\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I've looked into this thing myself, and a helluva lot of things don't add up...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.68,1:05:12.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于这件…警察怎么说的…怪异的意外事故\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}...about this... what are the cops calling it-- a freak accident?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.65,1:05:17.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我是说，那女孩呢？人人都假装她不在车里，而你见过她\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I mean, how about that girl-- everyone's pretending she wasn't even in the car. You saw her.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.06,1:05:19.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你的消息来源还说什么了？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What else did the source of yours say?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.15,1:05:23.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗯，除了其他事，还说你录下了那次枪击\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Well, among other things, that you recorded that gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.74,1:05:26.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,干得好，杰克，我想听听录音，在这里吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}That's great work, Jack. I'd sure like to hear the tape. Do you got it here?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.45,1:05:31.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 有何用处？那可能是我在录音棚伪造的  - 是有可能，但…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- All right, what good? I could've made it in a recording studio. - Well, you could have but...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.66,1:05:34.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我认为你不会\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I don't think you did.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.54,1:05:38.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我认为你录了带子，杰克，而且我认为是真的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I think you got a tape, Jack, and I think it's the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.09,1:05:40.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让我带你上电视\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Let me put you on the air.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.69,1:05:43.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在那里你可以告诉大家，那晚你看见什么，你听见什么\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}There you can tell everybody what you saw that night, you tell them what you heard.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.70,1:05:45.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后，砰…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}And then-- boom.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.20,1:05:49.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,咱们播出那带子，这是大事件，你说呢？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}We play that tape. It's a great story. What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.10,1:05:53.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 只是些胡说，没人相信它  - 嘿，弗兰克·唐纳休相信\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- It's bullshit. Nobody'd believe it. - Hey. Frank Donahue believes it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.68,1:05:58.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他可有8百万观众，杰克，8百万人每晚收看他\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}And he's got eight million people, Jack. Eight million people every night that watch him.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.31,1:06:01.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,跟我一起干，我跟你保证，到明晚8点30\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Go along with me on this. I guarantee you, by 8:30 tomorrow night,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.47,1:06:04.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那8百万狗杂种人人都会相信杰克·泰瑞说的故事\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}every one of those eight million sons of bitches will believe Jack Terry's story.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.93,1:06:06.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我跟你保证\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I promise you that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.19,1:06:48.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对，那就是我听到的，就在爆胎之前\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yeah, that's what I heard. Just before the tyre blew out.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.78,1:06:50.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你说对了，那是枪声\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You're right. It was a shot.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.07,1:06:52.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你把这个交给警察了？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}You took this to the police, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.00,1:06:55.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对，我给警察了，我给了他们一份拷贝\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Yes. I took this to the police. I gave them a copy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.36,1:06:57.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们送到实验室，发现是空白的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}They sent it to the lab and it was blank.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.25,1:06:59.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 所以有人洗掉了它  - 你肯定吗？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- So somebody's erased it. - Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.83,1:07:04.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我亲手转录的，我听过回放，现在却空白了，我其它的带子也是\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I transferred it myself, I heard it played back and now it's blank, like the rest of my tapes.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.63,1:07:10.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好，冷静，这声音非常清晰，就是图像有点模糊\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}OK. Calm down. The sound is very clear. It's the picture that's a little fuzzy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.30,1:07:11.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,糟糕，没人会信\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Shit. Nobody's gonna believe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.42,1:07:13.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们会说是我在实验室里制造的，而他们是对的\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}They'd say I made it up in the lab, and they'd be right.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.81,1:07:15.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不管主谋是谁，他已经联系过警方…\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Whoever's in on this has contacts with the police.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.87,1:07:18.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为他们想要麦克雷消失得无影无踪\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}Because they want McRyan to sink without a trace.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.06,1:07:20.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们不想听我说的枪声\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}They don't wanna hear about my gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.90,1:07:23.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 天，你打算怎么做？  - 什么？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- Gee, what are you gonna do? - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.11,1:07:24.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你打算怎么做？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What are you gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.44,1:07:26.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,什么我打算怎么做？是咱们打算怎么做？\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}What you mean what am I gonna do, what are we gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.53,1:07:29.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我跟这事有什么关系？  - 你别编了，莎莉\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}- What do I have to do with this? - You cut the shit, Sally.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.56,1:07:31.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我知道你在车里做什么\N{\fs10\1c&HB4DCFC&}I know what you were doin' in that car.
